                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 412.11/75.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Mexican Ambassador</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1235.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexican Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-04-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 1, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: In compliance with the instructions
                    received from my Government I have the honor to inform you that Mexico has <pb
                        facs="1077" n="961" xml:id="pg_961"/> named commissioners at El Paso, Texas,
                    and Douglas, Arizona, to attend to the claims for damages caused during the
                    combats that occurred at Ciudad Juárez and Agua Prieta.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gilberto Crespo y Martinez</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
